WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.320
This is how to set up your very first coding project using positron in less than 10 minutes.

00:00:04.320 --> 00:00:06.840
The first step is to create a folder and open it.

00:00:06.840 --> 00:00:10.120
You can do that using the terminal commands or just the normal file picker structure.

00:00:10.120 --> 00:00:12.280
You'll be prompted to pick your python interpreter.

00:00:12.280 --> 00:00:17.360
Step 2 is to install your commonly used packages like shiny and pandas using the pip command.

00:00:17.360 --> 00:00:20.840
Once those have installed, you can then use shiny create to create your scaffold of the

00:00:20.840 --> 00:00:21.840
shiny app.

00:00:21.840 --> 00:00:24.799
This will set up your app.py with starter UI and server code.

00:00:24.799 --> 00:00:26.320
Step number 3 is to run it.

00:00:26.320 --> 00:00:30.520
In positron, you can click the play button on the file itself, and it will automatically

00:00:30.520 --> 00:00:34.160
run your shiny app in the viewer pane, or you can run this command from the terminal.

00:00:34.160 --> 00:00:37.980
Using the flag for reload ensures that any edits you make in the app.py folder will show

00:00:37.980 --> 00:00:38.980
up immediately.

00:00:38.980 --> 00:00:42.799
And then for step 4, edit your file and watch it update in real time.

00:00:42.799 --> 00:00:46.320
Anytime you make a change and save the file, it will automatically reload in the app.

00:00:46.320 --> 00:00:49.560
And then for step 5, you can drop in a breakpoint for any debugging you need.

00:00:49.560 --> 00:00:52.560
Click on the left of the line number to set up a breakpoint, then click the dropdown arrow

00:00:52.560 --> 00:00:55.000
next to run, select debug shiny app.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:58.599
The app will pause right where you placed it, and now you can step through the lines,

00:00:58.599 --> 00:01:00.160
inspect variables, and see the call stack.

00:01:00.160 --> 00:01:02.720
Leave any questions in the comments below and follow along for more of our data science

00:01:02.720 --> 00:01:03.720
content.

